Description: The adaptation of the popular animated series continues as the crew of White Base discover a new weapon possibly even more valuable than their Mobile Suit.
Title: MOBILE SUIT GUNDAM: THE ORIGIN, VOL. 3
Author: Yoshikazu Yasuhiko and  Hajime Yatate
Contributor: by Yoshikazu Yasuhiko and  Hajime Yatate

Description: The Titans are closing in, but this time, they are not after the humans, but one of their own.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN, VOL. 7
Author: Hajime Isayama

Description: Laila and Leily's wedding day finally arrives, but will the ceremony and their grooms live up to their expectations?
Title: A BRIDE'S STORY, VOL. 5
Author: Kaoru Mori

Description: Maka and her demon scythe, Soul Eater, train in preparation for an attack from Noah and his followers.
Title: SOUL EATER, VOL. 16
Author: Atsushi Ohkubo

Description: Is this the end of humanity? It sure looks that way when what is left of mankind must go into hiding to escape the giant humanoids known as the Titans.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN, VOL. 1
Author: Hajime Isayama

Description: Mankind has gone into hiding to escape the giant humanoids known as the Titans. In this volume, a female Titan emerges who may have a human trapped within her.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN, VOL. 6
Author: Hajime Isayama

Description: A young man stumbles into Wonderland and assumes the role of "Alice" in this interpretation of Lewis Carrol's classic tale.
Title: ARE YOU ALICE, VOL. 2
Author: Ikumi Katagiri and Ai Ninomiya
Contributor: by Ikumi Katagiri and Ai Ninomiya

Description: Sailor Moon fights for justice in the name of the Moon and the mysterious Moon Princess. In this volume, high school shenanigans.
Title: SAILOR MOON SHORT STORIES, VOL. 1
Author: Naoko Takeuchi

Description: Mankind has gone into hiding to escape the giant humanoids known as the Titans. In this volume, the Titans attack, but one of them goes rogue.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN, VOL. 2
Author: Hajime Isayama

Description: A search party is organized after Shuusei and Tooko disappear while on a special mission in Kyoto.
Title: THE BETRAYAL KNOWS MY NAME, VOL. 6
Author: Hotaru Odagiri
